{"id":28162,"title":"Helping smokers quit improves health and budgets.","abstract":"(1) Treatment of smoking-related illnesses accounts for about 11 percent of Medicaid expenditures. (2) As of 2014, seven states provide comprehensive tobacco-cessation coverage to Medicaid enrollees, including individual counseling, group counseling, and seven types of U.S. Food and Drug Administration-approved medications. (3) Without assistance from medication or other forms of help, around 4 percent to 7 percent of quit attempts are successful; with tobacco-cessation medication use, the success rate is 25 percent.","date":"2014-07-02","categories":"Chemically-Induced Disorders","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24988614","annotations":[{"name":"Health","weight":0.683977,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Health"},{"name":"Food","weight":0.587908,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Food"},{"name":"Pharmaceutical drug","weight":0.525932,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pharmaceutical_drug"},{"name":"Medicaid","weight":0.318828,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Medicaid"},{"name":"Tobacco smoking","weight":0.304844,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tobacco_smoking"},{"name":"U.S. state","weight":0.128014,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/U.S._state"},{"name":"Budget","weight":0.0551856,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Budget"},{"name":"List of counseling topics","weight":0.0546925,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_counseling_topics"},{"name":"Comprehensive school","weight":0.0370044,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Comprehensive_school"},{"name":"Confederate States of America","weight":0.0301868,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Confederate_States_of_America"},{"name":"Formula One","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Formula_One"},{"name":"Musical ensemble","weig